         <abstract id="aspace_19515767472e7a8e6ea6a22729127e84">The collection contains glass plate and photographic negatives of scenes from World War I in France by Reverend George Fountain, including images of Sergeant Alvin York and General John J. Pershing, lantern slides of scenes from silent films by an unknown photographer, and motion picture films related to the Bible and physician Edward Livingston Trudeau and the Saranac Laboratory for the Study of Tuberculosis. Also included is a stereopticon used to project images from the lantern slides, which feature actors such as Marion Davies and Douglas Fairbanks, onto a movie screen.</abstract>
