            <scopecontent id="aspace_c62694275626cc481b461aadd8be53e8">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>This series contains twelve 35mm filmstrips of "Bible in Pictures," a film series created by the National Picture Company of Cincinnati, and one 35mm filmstrip related to Edward Livingston Trudeau and the Saranac Laboratory for the Study of Tuberculosis. The film canisters were formerly stored in a compartment of the stereopticon in Series II. Other materials include an unidentified fragment of a negative that may relate to silent film and a typed dinner invitation, also found in the stereopticon compartment.</p>
            </scopecontent>
